1.speaker: PENGUIN
1.definition: Miss Sasako, I want to try something other than a café mocha sometime.

2.speaker: PENGUIN
2.definition: What do you suggest? Let's see... I think a café mocha is perfectly fine.

3.speaker: PENGUIN
3.definition: Could you think about it a little longer, Miss Sasako?

6.speaker: POLAR BEAR
6.character: 新メニューで出そうと思って
6.definition: I've been thinking about adding this to the menu.

7.speaker: POLAR BEAR
7.definition: Want to try it? It's crab bread.

9.speaker: PENGUIN
9.character: じゃあ　それもらおうかな
9.definition: Sure, I'll give it a shot. Just came out of the oven.

11.speaker: PENGUIN
11.character: 基本　リアルさいらないんじゃないかなぁ
11.definition: I don't know that "realism" is really an important factor for bread.

12.speaker: POLAR BEAR
12.character: タラバガニのほうがよかった
12.definition: Would a red king crab have been better?

13.speaker: PENGUIN
13.character: 種類じゃなくて　表現の問題かな
13.definition: I don't think the species is the issue. I think it's the presentation.

14.speaker: PENGUIN
14.character: どうしたの パンダくん

15.speaker: PANDA
15.character: どうしてもバイト行きたくないんだよ
15.definition: I really don't want to go to work today.

16.speaker: PANDA
16.character: ペンギンさん　代わりにバイト行ってくれない？
16.definition: Will you go to work for me, Mr. Penguin?

17.speaker: PENGUIN
17.character: キミ…　年中　そんなこと言ってるね
17.definition: You say that all year long, don't you?

18.speaker: PANDA
18.character: いつもは ただの行きたくないだけどね
18.definition: Usually it's a normal feeling of not wanting to go, but I {\i1}really{\i0} don't want to go today.

19.speaker: PENGUIN
19.character: はい　そうですか 代わりに　バイト行きましょう
19.definition: "Oh, okay sure. Well, in that case, I'll totally go for you!"

20.speaker: PENGUIN
20.character: なんて言う人は　世界中探してもいないんじゃないかなぁ
20.definition: Do you think there's anybody in the world who'd say that?

21.speaker: POLAR BEAR
21.character: 青いバンダナ　シュッとほどいて…
21.definition: I fling off my blue bandana...

22.speaker: PENGUIN
22.definition: Apparently there was someone, and they were very close by.

23.speaker: PENGUIN
23.character: キミ　シロクマくんにちゃんとお礼言ったほうがいいよ
23.definition: You need to make sure you thank Polar Bear.

33.speaker: POPO
33.character: だから　こんなパンダがいるわけ…
33.definition: There's no way a panda would look like...

34.speaker: POLAR BEAR
34.definition: See? Could I please see your license {\i1}(menkyosho){\i0}? What?

43.speaker: POPO
43.character: シロクマじゃないですか

45.speaker: POPO
45.character: 紛らわしいこと やめてくださいよ

47.speaker: SASAKO
47.character: ほら　シロクマさんも
47.definition: Come on, Mr. Polar Bear. You too.

49.speaker: SASAKO
49.character: だから　ダメですって 言ったじゃないですか
49.definition: This is why I said you shouldn't do it. I'll make sure to walk next time.

50.speaker: SASAKO
50.character: そういう問題じゃありません

51.speaker: POLAR BEAR
51.character: それで　パンダくんは

52.speaker: SASAKO
52.character: 半田さんから電話があって 動物園に行きました
52.definition: He got a phone call from Mr. Handa and went to the zoo.

53.speaker: PANDA
53.character: ごめんね　シロクマくん

54.speaker: POLAR BEAR
54.character: いいの　いいの パンダくんのせいじゃないから
54.definition: It's no problem at all. It's not your fault, Panda.

55.speaker: PANDA
55.character: ねえ　シロクマくんが 懲役刑になった　おわびにさ…

56.speaker: POLAR BEAR
56.definition: You mean questioned by the police? Yeah.

57.speaker: PANDA
57.character: 職務質問になった　おわびにさ
57.definition: Since you were questioned by the police...

58.speaker: PANDA
58.character: 明日は１日 僕がカフェの仕事するから
58.definition: As an apology, I'll work at the café tomorrow.

59.speaker: PANDA
59.character: シロクマくんは１日休んでよ
59.definition: So you should take the day off, Polar Bear.

61.speaker: PANDA
61.definition: Okay? Take it easy, Polar Bear.

62.speaker: PENGUIN
62.character: どうしたの　パンダくん
62.definition: What's with you all a sudden, Panda?

63.speaker: POLAR BEAR
63.character: それじゃ　いってきます
63.definition: All right, I'll be off, then.

65.speaker: SASAKO
65.definition: Are you really going, Mr. Polar Bear?

66.speaker: POLAR BEAR
66.character: パンダくんに任せとけば 大丈夫　大丈夫
66.definition: Everything will be fine if we leave it to Panda.

67.speaker: SASAKO
67.character: おもしろがってません

71.speaker: GRIZZLY
71.definition: Why the hell are you drinking? That means I have to drive the whole time!

74.speaker: PANDA
74.definition: Miss Sasako, let's do our best.

77.speaker: PENGUIN
77.character: あっ　パンダくん ほんとに　バイトしてるの
77.definition: Oh, you were serious about working here part-time, Panda? Just for a day.

78.speaker: PANDA
78.character: 明日からは　いつも以上にのんびりするよ
78.definition: I'm going to be relaxing even more than usual starting tomorrow.

79.speaker: PENGUIN
79.character: その宣言はいらないんじゃないかな
79.definition: I don't think you need to announce that.

80.speaker: PANDA
80.character: でも　今日は頑張るよ
80.definition: But I'm going to work hard today.

83.speaker: PANDA
83.character: どうぞ　お水です ごゆっくり
83.definition: Here you go, have some water. Please take your time.

84.speaker: PENGUIN
84.character: パンダくん　僕　キミの前でどれだけカフェモカ飲んだかしれないよ
84.definition: Panda, I can't even count how many times I've had a café mocha in front of you.

86.speaker: PENGUIN
86.character: 今日は　お客さん来ないね
86.definition: There doesn't seem to be any customers coming today.

89.speaker: CUSTOMER2
89.definition: Looks like it. Let's try another day.

90.speaker: SASAKO
90.character: あれ　鍵が閉まってる

92.speaker: PANDA
92.character: 開けると　お客さん来ちゃうから 閉めといたよ
92.definition: If I unlocked the doors, customers would come in, so I kept them locked. Wha?

93.speaker: PANDA
93.character: いつも　シロクマくんが 忙しい忙しいって言ってるでしょ
93.definition: Polar Bear is always saying how busy he is, right?

94.speaker: SASAKO
94.character: そっか　気持は嬉しいけど 鍵は開けとこうね
94.definition: I see. I appreciate the concern, but let's keep the doors unlocked.

95.speaker: PANDA
95.character: わかった　お客さんは 来たほうがいいんだね
95.definition: Okay. So it's better if customers come, right?

96.speaker: PANDA
96.character: じゃあ　お客さん来たら どこまで　セルフサービスにする
96.definition: Then if we get customers, how much should we make the customers do themselves?

97.speaker: SASAKO
97.character: え～と　基本　うちは 全部　私たちでやるかな
97.definition: Um, we usually do it all ourselves.

99.speaker: LADY
99.definition: Do you have any seats open? Yes, but you'd be sharing a table with someone else. Is that all right?

103.speaker: SASAKO
103.character: すみません　あいたらすぐ別の席を用意しますから
103.definition: I apologize. We'll show you to another seat as soon as one opens up.

104.speaker: PANDA
104.character: ごゆっくり　どうぞ

105.speaker: GIRL
105.character: 注文　お願いします
105.definition: Could you take our order, please?

106.speaker: PANDA
106.character: あぁ　はい　今　行きます
106.definition: Oh, okay. I'll be right with you.

107.speaker: SASAKO
107.character: パンダくん　お料理よろしくね
107.definition: Don't forget about the food, too, Panda.

108.speaker: PANDA
108.definition: Okay. Thank you very much. I'm serious.

109.speaker: LADY
109.character: やだよ　この子ったら

110.speaker: LION
110.character: じゃあ　ばあちゃん　またな

112.speaker: SASAKO
112.character: あっ　シロクマさん お帰りなさい
112.definition: Oh, Mr. Polar Bear. Welcome back.

114.speaker: GRIZZLY
114.character: じゃあな　シロクマ

115.speaker: POLAR BEAR
115.definition: See you later. Oh, welcome back.

116.speaker: POLAR BEAR
116.character: ただいま　パンダくんは

117.speaker: SASAKO
117.character: いますよ　今日１日パンダくんほんとに頑張ってくれたんですよ
117.definition: He's here. Panda worked really hard all day today.

118.speaker: SASAKO
118.character: ペンギンさんが 手伝おうかって言っても僕やるからって
118.definition: Even when Mr. Penguin offered to help, he kept saying he'd do it himself.

119.speaker: PENGUIN
119.character: で　急に声がしなくなったと思ったら
119.definition: Then I noticed that I haven't heard him in a while...

123.speaker: POLAR BEAR
123.character: パンダくんに任せとけば大丈夫だって言ったでしょ
123.definition: I told you everything would be okay if we left it up to Panda.

125.speaker: PANDA
125.character: シロクマくんは休んでいてよ

126.speaker: POLAR BEAR
126.character: 気にしなくていいのに
126.definition: You don't need to be worried about that.

130.speaker: RIN RIN
130.definition: Thanks for your hard work. Here.

132.speaker: RIN RIN
132.character: またね 日曜日も頑張ってね
132.definition: See you later! Do your best on Sunday, too!

135.speaker: PENGUIN
135.character: どうしてもって言うなら

136.speaker: PENGUIN
136.character: 僕がイスに座る瞬間を見せてあげてもいいよ
136.definition: I'll show you how I get onto a chair.

137.speaker: SASAKO
137.character: すみません　今忙しいから パッとなら見ます
137.definition: I'm sorry, but I'm rather busy right now, so I'll look if it'll be quick.

138.speaker: PENGUIN
138.character: じゃあいいや　時間あるときで
138.definition: Never mind then. I'll do it when you have time.

141.speaker: POLAR BEAR
141.character: どうしてもって言うなら…

142.speaker: POLAR BEAR
142.character: 僕がアザラシじゃなく　セイウチを捕まえるところ 見せてあげるよ
142.definition: I'll show you how I catch a walrus, instead of a seal.

143.speaker: PENGUIN
143.character: そこは　ぜひ遠慮しとくよ
143.definition: I will gladly decline that offer.

146.speaker: PANDA
146.character: また　もらっちゃったよ…

148.speaker: PANDA
148.character: ペンギンさん　今から ダッシュで行って返してきてよ
148.definition: Would you go return these in a hurry for me, Mr. Penguin?

149.speaker: PENGUIN
149.character: ダッシュする必要あるかな
149.definition: Is there a reason for me to hurry?

150.speaker: RIN RIN
150.character: 今日もパンダくん かわいかったな
150.definition: Panda was so cute again today.

151.speaker: RIN RIN
151.character: いらっしゃい すみません　留守にしちゃって
151.definition: Welcome! Sorry to keep you waiting!

152.speaker: GIRL1
152.definition: Oh, it's fine. Um, Mr. Panda asked me to give you this letter.

153.speaker: RIN RIN
153.character: えっ　パンダくんから

154.speaker: RIN RIN
154.character: 本当　ありがとうございます

155.speaker: RIN RIN
155.character: 今夜８時　バードランドで待ってます
155.definition: I'll be waiting for you at Bird Land at 8 PM.

158.speaker: RIN RIN
158.definition: I hope this is the place.

161.speaker: RIN RIN
161.character: ああ　常勤パンダさん

162.speaker: RIN RIN
162.character: あの…　パンダくんは？

163.speaker: FT PANDA
163.definition: Why don't you take a seat?

164.speaker: RIN RIN
164.character: えっと　僕 パンダくんと待ち合わせなんですが
164.definition: Um... I'm supposed to be meeting up with Panda.

165.speaker: FT PANDA
165.character: ああそれね　あたし　あたし　あたしがね呼んだの
165.definition: Oh, I'm the one that sent that letter. I'm the one that invited you. But Panda—

166.speaker: FT PANDA
166.character: パンダくん　パンダくんって あたしだってパンダでしょ
166.definition: Oh, Panda this, Panda that... I'm a panda, too!

167.speaker: FT PANDA
167.character: まあ　座って ほら　いいから
167.definition: Come and have a seat. Come on.

169.speaker: FT PANDA
169.character: ビールでいいかな？　林さん
169.definition: Is beer okay with you, Mr. Hayashi?

173.speaker: PANDA
173.character: 誰かに　僕の　かわいさを 分けてあげたいんだよ
173.definition: I want to share a bit of my cuteness with someone.

174.speaker: PENGUIN
174.character: 相談の件　取り消していいかな
174.definition: Could I withdraw my offer to give advice?

175.speaker: PANDA
175.character: 僕　かわいさを 持て余しちゃってるんだよね

176.speaker: PENGUIN
176.character: 笹子さん　カフェモカ　おかわり
176.definition: Could I get another café mocha, Miss Sasako?

179.speaker: RIN RIN
179.character: あの…　常勤パンダさんが 僕に何の用ですか
179.definition: Pardon me, but, what exactly did you want with me, Mr. Full-time Panda?

180.speaker: FT PANDA
180.character: 林さん　あなた同じパンダなのに
180.definition: Mr. Hayashi. We're both pandas, but you're always going on and on about how cute Panda is.

181.speaker: FT PANDA
181.character: どうして　私のことは かわいいって言わないんですか
181.definition: Why don't you ever call me cute?

182.speaker: FT PANDA
182.character: あ～　お姉さん あたりめ　ちょうだい
182.definition: Hey, Miss! Could I get some dried squid?

184.speaker: FT PANDA
184.character: あと　枝豆　追加でね～
184.definition: Could you add on some edamame, too?

186.speaker: FT PANDA
186.character: ねぇ　どうしてなの

187.speaker: RIN RIN
187.character: そういうところですかね…
187.definition: I think it's subtle things like that.

188.speaker: FT PANDA
188.character: なにしたって　かわいいでしょう パンダなんだから
188.definition: Everything that I do should be cute! I'm a panda!

189.speaker: RIN RIN
189.definition: I wouldn't say that... Hey, Miss! Could I get some dried squid?

191.speaker: FT PANDA
191.character: 林さん　なに　ニマニマしてるの
191.definition: What are you grinning about, Mr. Hayashi?

193.speaker: RIN RIN
193.character: パンダくんで想像したら かわいかったから…
193.definition: I was imagining Panda saying that line, and it was really cute. What's so different? We're both pandas!

194.speaker: RIN RIN
194.character: 見ます　パンダくんのアルバム
194.definition: Do you want to see? It's a photo album of Panda.

195.speaker: FT PANDA
195.character: いつも　持ち歩いてるの
195.definition: Do you always carry that around?

196.speaker: RIN RIN
196.character: 今日パンダくんと 一緒に見ようと思って
196.definition: I wanted to go through it with Panda today,

198.speaker: RIN RIN
198.character: ほら　かわいいでしょう
198.definition: See? Look how cute he is.

199.speaker: FT PANDA
199.character: 確かに　かわいいな～　あたしは
199.definition: Yeah, he is cute. And me?

200.speaker: RIN RIN
200.character: そうですね… 若干　疲れている気がします
200.definition: Well, I think you look a bit tired.

201.speaker: FT PANDA
201.character: そうだね　くたびれてるね

202.speaker: RIN RIN
202.character: これは　掃除機に吸われて 寝グセがついたままのパンダくんです
202.definition: Here's a picture of Panda with bedhead after being sucked up by a vacuum.

206.speaker: RIN RIN
206.character: そうですね…　内職してますね
206.definition: Well... You're doing a side job.

207.speaker: LLAMA
207.character: 生活感　ありますね
207.definition: You can get a sense of how he lives from that picture.

209.speaker: LLAMA
209.character: 僕も　一緒にいいですか

211.speaker: FT PANDA
211.character: じゃあ　まず　一杯

212.speaker: LLAMA
212.character: ありがとうございます

213.speaker: LLAMA
213.character: けど　写真に撮ってもらえるだけ いいですよ
213.definition: At least you get pictures taken of you.

214.speaker: LLAMA
214.character: 僕なんて お客さん　みんな素通りですよ
214.definition: Everyone always passes right by me.

215.speaker: RIN RIN
215.character: あっ　動物園の方でしたか
215.definition: Oh, so you work at the zoo, too?

217.speaker: WAITRESS
217.character: ビールとあたりめです
217.definition: Here's your beer and dried squid.

220.speaker: RIN RIN
220.character: あ…　そういうの　やめたほうが…
220.definition: I don't think that's a good ide—

222.speaker: RIN RIN
222.definition: Yes? You must be really popular.

223.speaker: RIN RIN
223.definition: You don't handle alcohol well, do you?

226.speaker: FT PANDA
226.character: かわいく見られたいよ～ リンランさ～ん
226.definition: I want to be seen as cute, Mr. Rin Ran.

228.speaker: RIN RIN
228.character: 常勤パンダさん　大丈夫ですか
228.definition: Are you all right, Mr. Full-time Panda?

229.speaker: FT PANDA
229.character: 明日　動物園　来てよ～

230.speaker: RIN RIN
230.character: 明日は パンダくん　いないじゃないですか…
230.definition: But Panda won't be there tomorrow.

231.speaker: FT PANDA
231.character: あたしが　いるでしょう

234.speaker: RIN RIN
234.character: わかりました　行きますよ

235.speaker: FT PANDA
235.character: ありがとう　リンロンさ～ん

238.speaker: FT PANDA
238.character: やぁ　林さん いや～　ありがとう　ありがとう
238.definition: Hey, Mr. Hayashi. Thank you very much.

239.speaker: RIN RIN
239.character: 僕　パンダなら 基本 かわいいと思うんですけど…
239.definition: I do think that pandas are cute in general...

240.speaker: RIN RIN
240.character: なんで　常勤パンダさんはそんなに かわいくはないんだろう
240.definition: So I wonder why you aren't that cute, Mr. Full-time Panda...

244.speaker: FT PANDA
244.character: 今　パッと済ませちゃうから
244.definition: I'll finish it up real quick.

246.speaker: FT PANDA
246.character: お客さん少ない日は 結構はかどるんだよ
246.definition: I can get through it quite quickly when there aren't any customers around.

247.speaker: RIN RIN
247.character: それ…　やめましょうか

248.speaker: RIN RIN
248.character: 内職するパンダなんて かわいくないでしょ
248.definition: Pandas doing side jobs aren't cute.

250.speaker: PANDA
250.character: よいしょ　よいしょ

252.speaker: RIN RIN
252.definition: I wonder if it's a matter of potential...

253.speaker: FT PANDA
253.character: ちょっと…　諦めないでよ
253.definition: Hey, don't give up on me.

254.speaker: RIN RIN
254.character: じゃあ　タイヤで遊んでみましょうか
254.definition: Well then, how about we have you play with a tire? Sure...

255.speaker: FT PANDA
255.definition: How's that? It's cute, but only slightly.

256.speaker: RIN RIN
256.character: あぁ　すみません でも大丈夫ですよ
256.definition: Oh, I'm sorry! But you'll be fine!

259.speaker: FT PANDA
259.character: そこそこの かわいさでいいのかな
259.definition: I wonder if I'll be okay being only slightly cute.

260.speaker: RIN RIN
260.character: 常勤パンダさんに 悪いことしちゃったなぁ
260.definition: I feel bad for what I did to Mr. Full-time Panda.

261.speaker: LLAMA
261.definition: Pardon... Oh, Mr. Llama! I'm sorry!

262.speaker: RIN RIN
262.definition: I was just looking for you.

263.speaker: RIN RIN
263.character: あっ　忘れてないです…　よ
263.definition: I didn't forget about you... at all!

266.speaker: KID
266.character: 頑張って　パンダさ～ん
266.definition: Do your best, Mr. Panda! Look over here!

267.speaker: KID
267.character: はぁ…　やっぱりパンダくんにはかなわないなぁ
267.definition: So cute! I guess I can't beat Panda.

268.speaker: PANDA
268.definition: I'm finally done! Thanks for your hard work, Panda! Here, take this!

271.speaker: GIRL
271.character: あの…　一緒に 写メ撮ってもらえますか
271.definition: Um, will you take a cell phone picture with us?

274.speaker: GIRL
274.character: お花持ってるパンダさんもかわいい
274.definition: A panda holding flowers is so cute!

276.speaker: RIN RIN
276.definition: Do your best next week, too!

277.speaker: RIN RIN
277.character: やっぱり人気者だな かわいいもんな
277.definition: He really is popular. Well, he is cute.

280.speaker: GIRLIE
280.definition: Mr. Panda! Oh, Panda already le—

283.speaker: GIRLIE
283.character: こっちのパンダさんだもん
283.definition: I wanted to see you! Here!

287.speaker: GIRLIE
287.character: ママ　パンダさんに渡せた
287.definition: I got to give them to Mr. Panda, Mommy! Really? Good for you.

288.speaker: GIRLIE
288.character: うん　じゃあね　バイバーイ

292.speaker: SASAKO
292.character: 座る瞬間　見ますよ　じっくり
292.definition: I'll watch you as you sit! Very attentively!

295.speaker: PENGUIN
295.character: そんなあらためて 見せるものでもないよ
295.definition: It's not that big of a deal.

297.speaker: PANDA
297.character: ペンギンさん　ペンギンさん

299.speaker: PANDA
299.character: 今頭に浮かんだ話してよ
299.definition: Tell us the first thing that comes to mind.

300.speaker: PENGUIN
300.character: カラオケで　サビのところでちょっとずれちゃったとき
300.definition: When you miss the chorus of a song by a little bit when you're singing karaoke,

301.character: どうごまかしたら恥ずかしくないかなぁって
301.definition: how do you recover without embarrassing yourself?

302.speaker: PANDA
302.character: もっと情熱的に話して

304.speaker: PENGUIN
304.character: なるべくこっそりしたい話だよ
304.definition: It's something I'd rather talk about quietly.
